tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE volunteer_hours (
  volunteer_id INT NOT NULL,
  employee_id INT NOT NULL,
  hours_worked INT NOT NULL,
  date_worked DATE NOT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (volunteer_id),
  FOREIGN KEY (employee_id) REFERENCES employees(employee_id)
);

CREATE TABLE employee_programs (
  employee_id INT NOT NULL,
  program_id INT NOT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (employee_id, program_id),
  FOREIGN KEY (employee_id) REFERENCES employees(employee_id),
  FOREIGN KEY (program_id) REFERENCES programs(program_id)
);

CREATE TABLE Employee (
    employee_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    department VARCHAR(50),
    email VARCHAR(50),
    total_hours INT
);

CREATE TABLE VolunteerEvent (
    event_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    event_name VARCHAR(50),
    location VARCHAR(50),
    date DATE,
    hours_required INT
);

CREATE TABLE EmployeeVolunteer (
    employee_id INT,
    event_id INT,
    hours_worked INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (employee_id, event_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (employee_id) REFERENCES Employee(employee_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (event_id) REFERENCES VolunteerEvent(event_id)
);

CREATE TABLE employee_volunteer_hours (
    employee_id INT,
    event_id INT,
    hours_worked INT NOT NULL,
    PRIMARY KEY (employee_id, event_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (employee_id) REFERENCES employees(employee_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (event_id) REFERENCES volunteering_events(event_id)
);

CREATE TABLE Employee (
    employee_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    first_name VARCHAR(50),
    last_name VARCHAR(50),
    email VARCHAR(100),
    department VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE VolunteerHours (
    volunteer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    date DATE,
    hours_spent INT,
    project_name VARCHAR(100),
    employee_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (employee_id) REFERENCES Employee(employee_id)
);

CREATE TABLE Projects (
    project_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    project_name VARCHAR(100),
    description TEXT,
    start_date DATE,
    end_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE EmployeeProjects (
    employee_id INT,
    project_id INT,
    PRIMARY KEY (employee_id, project_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (employee_id) REFERENCES Employee(employee_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (project_id) REFERENCES Projects(project_id)
);
